text.__SUMMARY__:
Quercus kiukiangensis is an uncommon Asian species of trees in the beech family. It has only been found in Tibet and Yunnan.
Quercus kiukiangensis is a large tree up to 30 meters tall. Leaves can be as much as 18 cm long.
